Yes, always. Yes. Mum was always on the head. My father the other side and we were each side, Min and I you know, yes. That's right. That - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 And your aunt and your cousin were on another table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 On a little table in the corner, yes. Little round table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How was the meal served, by whom, did your mother serve it straight from the saucepan onto the plates or did you have it on the table?

