\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, I don't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was your mother a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. Mum never bothered, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you remember her working for a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How do you mean? Spent all his time in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Yes. Oh he'd a marvellous - I'm not saying that 'cos it's dad like, - but he'd a marvellous garden. Yes. And grew beautiful flowers and all that you know, lovely, yes. And mother was more for sewing see, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well mum used to like to go to lectures if she could, she used to love that, she used to love lectures - if she could spare the time to go you know. She used to love anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Only with the church. You couldn't say that she went to pictures or anything like that, no, never, only to church, anything connected with the church she was always there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 With whom would she go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Some of the friends of the chapel you know, or if there's anything like - collections for different occasions you know as they do mother used to go then with friends from the church. Like if they were collecting f
or the missionary or sometimes they used to go round the houses didn't they years ago, 'cos they do it more in church now don't they. But years ago they never used to, mum used to go round collecting for things like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 When did your father get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - around about five o'clock every evening, that is his time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - well you could say that he was mostly in the garden you see and all that, because apa
rt from the allotment we had a big garden up in the house you see. Great big garden there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was the allotment near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Not very near, no, it was - tidy step to that. Used to go down - well about - it'd be about - mile and a half, something like that
, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. No clubs or pubs, nothing like that. Dad would never a drinker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your mother ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, I don't think so, no. No, he never - no, he never went to football matches or anything like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did he bet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, like a boot club or a sick club or a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
No. Well - I could tell you years ago - when I was work - where I - where I was working like, mum used to have a club there. And the clubs years ago not like they are today, you know, you had to have it at the end of the year. But because we were w
orking in there mum used to have a club like that. Then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 It was a clothing club was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Used to have it out then on Christmastime you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you get on with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh fine. Like you and Stella.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - the children round about you know and my sister see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Mostly, yes, all neighbours -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 On the mountains mostly, 'cos we had the tips you know were all around us you see, 
we were off the road then like and we could play at the tip where mum could see us you see. 'Cos there's a row of houses like and then the tips behind us. But they were more like mountains than tips you know, all nice green - grass. Yes. And she used to w
atch us up there and all, all - we always had to go up there to play where she could keep an eye on us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh dear, well - children's games and that you know, mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were you allowed to get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh dear, you were more dirty than ever clean, get on the tips and everywhere, yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh no. Mum was very funny like that. Awfully funny like that, yes. She was always afraid you know in case something would 
happen to us always, she was always nervous of things like that, fair play.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did she discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Why do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - well I - my mother used to think they were more rough you kn
ow, aren't they in the country like - you know what I mean. So we were awfully funny like that wasn't she. Well you don't remember, no. We shouldn't play with everybody like. Mum was always afraid of rows, put it like that, you know, don't come in if you'
re quarrelling and all like that you know, she never liked anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was it rather rough there then, a rough place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - the boys seemed to be more rough, you know what I mean, they were more country like, weren't they, they are rough
er really than the towns aren't they. You know. Well they're more for - animals and all that like that weren't they and horses and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, only the church - all with the church we had you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you spend your free time when you were at school, did you have any hobbies? Did you keep any pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. No, we just - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, for dad, we were helping dad mostly, yes, we would help him like. An
d - we always used to - put the seed potatoes and all like that ready you know. YES? Always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would you do any fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. But my father did that. My father - you see. Not fishing, poaching he was. Did a lot of that, we were frightened stif
f always with him. But he always got away with it you know, the farmers were marvellous and they never used to tell him off anything. Dad used to bring - trout - often when he was walk - walking the mountains you see, now he used to see the brooks see, he
'
d have for the brooks they - fishing. But if he was caught mind he'd have - he'd be fined for it, but he didn't bother. Often we had a trout you know. Well years ago I don't think they saw any - evil in anything did they, you understand what I mean, peopl
e were more friendly. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You mentioned earlier that you used to go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. NA.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well only with the school, you know, like used to have sports for the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You didn't play any games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Oh yes. We used to go to theatres then. You know, Theatre Royal in Merthry, used to go there when they had their shows there, you know, the Maid of the Mountains and - all that kind of - show.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Yes, regular to concerts. Yes. Especially at Good Friday. Used to go off to Ffesta, used to have marvellous concerts then, oh yes, wonderful. Went regular. Never missed it, never missed a Good Friday there, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
YES? WE used to go to the music hall, temperance hall we used to call it, you know, where they had variety and all that. We never missed any of those. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well they used to be
 a treat - to go to the cinema years ago like. We only used to go with mum or my aunt, one of the two like. Never go on our own, Minnie and I, used to be always one or the other with us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 When 
we started working. Never before that, no. They used to treat us to many things you know like but never pocket money 'til we started working. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No relations, friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, they never but if there was sickness they'd come in you know like, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 If your mother was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well, one of us there all the time see, Min or - myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Your aunt as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Mum was very lucky really, she had fairly good health you know - 'til the latter part when we were down here then you see, I was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about when you were a child, you did say that some neighbours would come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Oh yes, yes, they would help, fair play, yes. So - and if mum was ill or - my aunt wouldn't go to work or anything then see, we - we were very close like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby? You had your aunt and your grandmother and your cousin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 In the house you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you have any other relatives living near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Not many, no. They were a good - good bit - good way from us like, there was mum's brother, he was living in Georgetown. Mum had seven si
sters. And one brother. And the youngest of them was - was the brother and of course they worshipped him and that see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 They weren't living in Merthyr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 In Merthyr, yes, but they were far from us you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How much did you see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Mostly on Sundays, when we go to chapel, used to come to the same chapel, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes, they'd a lot of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well they sometimes - well they mostly used to come home you 
know to see them like. Mum - well mum was rather awkward with my aunt - with my - my - and my - and my aunt got ill in the end you see, she had angina. Mum never used to leave her very much. Always used to depend mostly depend on me than Minnies, used to 
say - she used to ask me, you going out so and so tonight, if there was a drama or if there was something in the church or anything, I used to stop in then for her to go to have a little night out you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would she have friends coming in to see her when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. They were calling in and out you know. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your father have friends, or would they have the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well about the same, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you think your mother had friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 W
ell she had friends of her own but they weren't in Merthyr though. They were out and mum used to come down here to see friends, to Cardiff. But they were school friends you know she used to visit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 When would she come to see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - abo
ut once a week sometimes, yes, and - yes, or they would come up like, yes, she spent a bit of time in Cardiff, you know. Before we ever came down here like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about when you were children? Did she have friends of her own then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well school friends. Yes. Kept up with them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about your father, did he have friends of his own like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, I think he did, I - I think he had them like more with the work you know, with his work like, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well I - how can I tell - it was on Sunday night now like if they'd come from the chapel they'd all come to the - you know. And in the weekday after there'd be friends from the chapel calling you know, oh yes, plenty of - friends we had always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes, always cup of tea before they'd go you know, the usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 On any particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well no, when they felt like it I think you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your father's friends or both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well both I should say really, yes. There wasn't one different to the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 When?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well it was mostly like when they were sick or - you know, like, or come in and have a chat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would neighbours call in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh - yes. We had a lovely lot of neighbours. The old lady opposite, mu
m used to worship - her anyway. 'Cos she used to come in like, an old lady, and the funny thing about it, they - when I was born they wanted to adopt me. Couple across, yes. Used to tell mum, oh, she said, you've got Minnie, let me have Doris. No, mum sai
d
 she wouldn't part one of them, she said, the only two I've got. Oh they were very very keen you know, well they were lovely couple too, fair play. They didn't have any children of their own. But - oh they were - they worried mum no end about me you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well sometimes I could say that you see because mum was awfully tied you know, it was very awkward really for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amus
ements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh have a sing-song round the organ and all that we used to do, yes, we had no end of fun like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Many people divide society into different social cla
sses or groups, in the time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well how do you mean now? Because - there were groups. I'll put it like this, now there were groups come into the Gyfarthfa church, and my mother used to look up to. Yes. Always used to look up to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well they was - it was something out of the ordinary really, like you know, and it used to be lovely to seem them coming you know in their horse and traps. Remember yea
rs ago, like. And how they used to - hold their - clothes if you remember if they had these skirts, they used to fold them over their arms. Well there were several people used to look up to then, like doctors and all that you know. They were class you kno
w what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were there any other groups then do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I don't think so, mostly they were - mostly the working class otherwise you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What class or group would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh the working class we are I think. Really like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What sort of people would belong to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 All my friends mostly, isn't it, you know all our friends like, all working class we are isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What sort of people belonged to the other class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
All the people that tried to be high ups like. Didn't bother much about them really. There are several we know mind, but we don't bother with 'em you know. They're a little bit beyond on you like, well at least they try to be beyond you don't they. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about Merthyr then in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh it was - wonderful. Indeed it was. Really - really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were there different groups or classes of people there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well, yes. There were a lot, there was - people - what shall I say now, you
 know the gaffers we used to call them years ago isn't you know, the gaffers and - cracher we used to call them don't they years ago, horrid is to be a cracher like, oh yes. You sort of look up to them like don't you you know, even in the churches you loo
ked up to them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What sort of people were they do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well of course they were - they moved with a different class to us like don't they you know, I mean they're - education to start with isn't it. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well sort of you had to use your head didn't you. You know, to be placid with everyone isn't it, you had to be careful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I never used to curtsey but we always used to watch our p's and q's like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 To whom would you have to show respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well I mean - well take doctors to start with isn't it, 'cos years ago we thought they were wonderful didn't we, and th
en the manager of the works after, then my - my father's - boss like, all things - you know, we had to do that didn't we. It was our nature to do it really wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, where I worked. You know, my gov'nor, always used to say sir to him you see when I - started working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did he own the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Or was she the manager?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Owned the shop, yes. The first one I worked with he owned the shop, Oh and the second, Artie Jones. Nev
er heard of them did you? Oh big people in Merthyr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well I think so, yes. Specially the - relatives and all the children of relatives isn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 In Merthyr then who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well I should say the managers and the miner - of the miners to start with you know, and then the steel works. Crawshaw, that's another one. People like that, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, I didn't. No. I think that I went through my father, you see my father hadn't anything to do with - the works you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Why were they considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well I think people had to watch out didn't they for their livelihood didn't they you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about the shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well we were - well - well mostly with the working class I should say. Because the working class really were given their - money to them isn't it, more so really than the - high ups isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Who do you think the clergy associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well I think the most - in Merthyr mostly with the working class, myself, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well they thought they - well I don't know, they - they se
emed to be different altogether don't they. Oh they did in Merthyr. Yes, they thought they were - they were it you know. And if you were working sort of thing well you were nobody. Honest, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You felt that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, they did, they showed i
t too. Because when they used to come in and - and there was other people we couldn't stick where - what do call it, when they were in - in the shops you know. Couldn't bear serving 'em, they're the worst people of all years ago. They did - they wanted so
 
much attention, you understand what I mean like. And Saturdays - used to have Saturdays - with the teachers, honest, yes. That's not nasty saying that, like, but they used to you know, they want - because - oh you'd pull a shop to pieces and perhaps they 
wouldn't buy anything. Couldn't stick them. Not any of us. We all used to hate Saturday. Funny isn't it. They needed so much attention see, that's what it was you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Who do you think they associated with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well they associated - tried to assoc
iate with the high ups didn't they, more or less like. My - don't think that, only they were so fidgety you know. Oh gosh we used to - what do you call it - and they - they thought they were it you know like and, oh I know so and so, I see him at the door
 there, there's not - and all that business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about farmers, were there any farmers then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well was one or two I knew of isn't there, farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh working class. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about employers in the district, there were a lot in Merthyr then weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Are you going now with the bosses or - where I - I worked liked isn't it. Yes. Gyfarthfa, yes. Gyfafthfa works you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Who would they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh with the elite of the - of Merthyr really they did. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well that's what I liked about the church years ago. Because there was everybody. And you were all classed a lik
e years ago weren't you, didn't matter who you were really whether you were - managers or bosses and this and that, you were all the same. But it's so different today somehow. You - you know, you - you sort of - could look up to them and speak to them cou
ldn't you. But we had a lot in our chapel I know as we had - we had most of the ones that - bosses, like the fruiterers you know and - fruit merchants. That type we had you see in Ynysgaeth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about the church there as different from the chapel? Who went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Oh Gyfarthfa church you mean, that's the only - Gyfarthfa church and - now our - my boss you see was a big noise in - St David's church. Very very strict - you know, from St David\rquote s there. You've seen that church haven't you. But
 Gyfarthfa church is lovely though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Who would go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well not any of our family like, but more of the crocha from the town like. 'Cos it was well noted, Gyfarthfa church you see 'cos it was - sort of in line with the Crawshaws and all that type you know. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living, or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well they were mostly about the same with us you see because - more or less like we were t
he working class that - like that you ought to - work things out for yourself, you understand what I mean, the - they never had - a lot of money, so - they depended a lot really on the gardens and stuff like that didn't they you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would you think that one group in the working class would feel superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 If they had a higher job, they would that, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes, several like that, yes. Yes. That's when my
 mother - mother - that's when mum wouldn't let us play with any of those, I mean, well it's the way they were brought up really isn't it you see. See sort of brought up more my own we used to say in Welsh you know. But some of them used to be - brought u
p rough, specially if they were more in family weren't they you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 There were big families were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh big families, yes, big families round our place you know, five - some of them had eight, nine children you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I don't think so, no. Only the working class mum did really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I think so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you remember a distinction at all between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
They're own craftsman - their own craftsmanship - you mean is it? Well I don't think so. I don't think so, not while we were living, no, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another? To go from the working class to the upper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, I don't think, no, no, I can't remember - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes, several I remember that up our way anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Why do you think they were described that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - the - the attitude isn't it. You can always tell can't you about people - by the attitude can't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you remember anybody called a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. I do that. Especially in the chapel and things you know, yes. Kindness you know, fair play. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh - several round where we lived. Yes. Well it's a country place, like we we
re out in the country you know living. Oh yes, there was several round our -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 It was on the edge of Merthyr was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 That's right, yes. Put it down and I'll tell you then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What did you think of the policemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well got on very well with 
them you know. We - we used to have no end of fun with them really to tell you honesty. They used to come and tell us they jokes you know, what - what they - they were very kind though to us really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did they treat the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh, marvellous they were I must say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes, certain times they did, fair play, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well it was the
n - about then I think I we started working, you know, Min and I like and we thought we were so thrilled like to help mum you know, like, 'cos I must give her - credit - fair play, for in her struggle she gave us our apprenticeship as we had to have three
 
years without anything you see, and Min, fair play for her you know. And I remember when I worked first with the half a crown I had for - for wages once. And I had to work for that, was on commission, you know, of course you had to - well like the teacher
s then didn't they, they had to - yes, we had three years apprenticeship you see, she and I did. Had to go through it all you know from different departments you see, work up from the - fancy department right up to the - gowns. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well dad was very fortunate really. Never very ill you see, fair play, very fortunate like that you know. But - as I just said, when Min and I came to earn like we helped - well we had to help you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You don't remember your father being out of work really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Not really, no, only when he was - when he - retired then you know like yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you ever get help from the Guardians or the Parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, thank -
 no indeed, mum was very funny like that. No. Very funny you know, no. Would rather do something outside you know before she - but we were very lucky like that, mind we never had big wages. It was when my - when we both started earning like that - see tha
t's why I got married late in life, it was thirty-one when I got married. And it helped home with his parents you see, for a time. So I mean mother sort of - more come on her feet then when we were - helping see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 When there was someone in the district whom people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
To some people they did because - oh I don't think I'd be wrong in saying this, I'll tell you what - one thing, when they used to come down from the North you
 know, North Walians, they were different again to us, altogether aren't they as you know. I mean they - they never - to start with they never lived like us did they? No, Their - their attitude was different altogether. And I know one person to came to li
ve - but my mum wasn't very - what do you call it - but - they were never brought - didn't bring the children like us you understand what I mean, they had to shift and which they do now. The North Walians are different altogether. You know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 A lot of North Walians came to Merthyr didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
At the time, yes, North Walians you see. YES? Then - Spaniards came a lot up there, well they came to Dowlas more than to Tolaspoint, yes. No, they weren't very keen at all on the North Walians were us. I must say that because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Why do you think it was, did they show it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well they - well their attitude is different from ours you see, they were - they weren't so warm I don't fancy, you understand what I mean, they were selfish. We never liked them, tell you straight, and I don't like them today myself -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was there any way in which the people of the town showed this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well they sort of never bothered like did they you know. Sort of - ignored it more or less like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were you given lessons by one of your parents at all, a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well mum used to tell us you see, mother used to al - she always used to watch that, oh yes, we had to listen to mum. And if there's anything in school that we couldn't do you know used to - u
sed to make us do it then if we had homework. Now you do it first and then she'd say - help us then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Five I think I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you remember what time of the morning you went and what time you came back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well mum used to take us then you know like because we'd such a tie - we had a good step to go you see, take us in the morning and then perhaps my aunt or someone come and fetch us home you know, 'til we got big enough to go with the other children.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you go all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you come home for the dinner hour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Oh yes, come home to dinner, yes. Oh come to meet us then when we were small. One or the other you see, yes. Well there was no dinners at school then you see, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 It was a lovely school. Very nice school - Georgetown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was it boys or girls or mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, they weren't mixed. Girls, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 It was a board school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Walk it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh about twenty minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well either my mother or my aunt you see, one of those two take us like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 And your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, and the both
 of us, yes. Unless they were friends, if there were friends going like then they - they - bring us like and then they'd change with mother you know, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well on times I liked it, on other times I didn't like it. You know. Some - yes. You know how it is, some - some subjects you liked, other subjects you didn't like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh they were lovely. Fiar play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did they emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well what they taught you you know in different -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Manners, tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Ways of speaking?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. All that see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh it'd be - behind the board then with dunces cap on your head wouldn't you years ago see isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did they punish the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well that's what mostly they used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 It was only girls there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Only girls where we - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What did you have to do to be put behind the board?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Either whether you shout or - or - you know - say something out of place, you know, if anybody would ask you a question an
d then you - you shout and answer it, well - wasn't it.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes, mum did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Always. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did they visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, som
etimes mum used to visit - she knew the teachers there you know. But of course with that you see we couldn't go on in school, we never had the money you see. Mother would have liked one of us to take a - now my sister was very musical you see, she would h
ave liked to have been a - a music teacher, something like that, but we never had the - so mother sacrificed herself to go and have her apprenticeship in the - the drapery you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you think the teachers singled out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well they had their - although I was very lucky though, I mean the teachers are very kind to me always, yes, yes, but I had the board you know. The photo with the board holding. Well there was - everything you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Yes, I - well we - yes, there were, but I - we weren't - I wasn't there - you know, I had to go home, I wasn't in the playground very much you know, we had to go home, yes. Yes. Yes, I didn't have chance y
ou see. Did that with chapel and all. We had to do it see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well some of them were very funny, you know what I mean, some are aren't they - in their - their own sphere aren't they, they - you k
now, they'd rather be - on their own or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you go on to another school after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. The one school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would you have stayed longer if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh if we had it, but - we never had it you see. No. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. I never bothered then, I - as I told you we went to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well sometimes I have. 
You know, we could have gone on a bit further if we'd had the means you see. But - I was satisfied in the drapery mind. We were all right there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes - definitely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means or earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Your first job when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Apprenticed in the drapery you see, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I had that really through
 my sister. First of all I didn't want to go into the drapery you see, I would rather have done something else. But - dad - we followed him really in his - line you see, yes, you see. So mum thought, well, Min being in the shop like, she thought that I'd 
do the same you know, so that's what I did. So I had three years there for nothing, Minnie found me the job really like, she wanted me to come there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - we had to - tidy up you know like and then you 
had to go - we had lessons with - with our boss you see in the dining room, taught us what to do and the measurements and all that. We had - went through all that, you know, like. And how to serve customers and how to approach them. All that. And how to t
idy everything you know, in the proper manner and different sizes. Of course years ago was different to what it is today you see, 'cos they - they don't do it today. I mean it's large, small and colour today isn't it, 'cos we had to do - W, WX and 
\endash  out size all that today - years ago like. It's easier for them today isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Nine in the morning 'til seven. And Saturday nine - nine 'til nine. YEs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, not Sunday work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you have a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Thursday afternoon. Finished at one, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Not then. No. No. Not when we were working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - when I started first - know how much I was having? Fifteen shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was that when you started at fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh no. Three years - and then you had to - you had to work on your - whatever you sold you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You had commission for the first three years?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh no. No. We worked the three years for nothing, th
en - then the - the third - the fourth year - no. Two years for nothing, the third year you worked on commission, and we never had much chance because we were - the lower - you know, the higher ups and that you see. And my first - first money was a half a
 crown. YES. And then that went on then you see after the three years you had five shillings. And in the fourth year you had - seven and six. That's how you were going, but when I left it was only a pound a week. YES. And from nine 'til nine then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
No, I didn't, we were all scribbling about that you see, yes. Of course I - I must say this - we had to work on commission. And I had very good commission. I must say that, I done very well with that. So that was making u
p for my - wages, but we had to earn it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would you have the commission on top of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 About how much would you have then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well very often I used to knock out about six pound a month. Every month we were paid yes.
 And then it was at the sale, you see, white sales or the - January sales you know. You could knock out a good bit then like. But of course that - yes. Not the same every month because the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What would be the less you'd have and what wo-ld be the most?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well - the least would be about a pound - being that I was - more or less only just - not so long come off my apprenticeship you see, you know like. And you had to take the third part all the time. See, 'cos there was second sales and first sales y
ou see. Yes, used to do all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, I give it all. To mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What was it spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh mother used to put some of it away for us mostly you know like and if we wanted anything then
, 'cos we had to dress in work, had to be tidy you know. Mother always put something away for us like. And then to help with the wages in the house you know, the food and everything in the house. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Not too bad. Some good, some bad you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Oh not too bad. Really speaking like we should have had more wages you know, but - we had to watch you see or else we could - we - might have been put out
, 'cos of the times you see, it was during the wartime and all that like. And of course - sales were up and down you know, if it was a good week well you'd be all right and - sometimes you'd have short time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - go
od and bad, we put it like that. Never liked much of their outlook considering he was supposed to be Christians you know in the church, that's what used to annoy me - very much too. They'd follow this and that in the church and then - they wouldn't treat 
their assistants as they should. I found that down here the same. I had to work during the war down here see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh I liked the work very much, yes, yes. Yes, I liked the work very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did it the one job you had in Merthyr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you stay in the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
No, well - why I had - we had short time, and I didn't stay then - to go back, I had a job in a - in - Artie Jones. Well in fact I had a job down here in Howells. I was going to come down 
here and mother wrote a letter to say that I wasn't to come. She stopped me coming. She wouldn't let me go see, nor my aunt. It was my aunt more than anything really like. She ddirn I myrd lawn co, she said, I gnerdydd with ei lunain. So I shouldn't go. I
 was soft really, I had a job like. But then mother wrote a letter - to tell him without me knowing. When I came home that night then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What did you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - no, you're not going down there she said to Cardiff, no fear. You shan't go down th
ere, she said. So I had to wait then and - indeed I didn't wait long before I had a job then at Artie Nones. A shop lower down. Drapery, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Hours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Nine 'til nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 The same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Nine 'til seven, and nine 'til nine on Saturday, yes. As I say, don't know they're born today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What were you paid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Same rate - same - same wage. Started there at fifteen shillings a week, there like
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you have commission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well it wasn't too bad if you had decent - commission see you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, give it all to mum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you get on with the other people you worked with there now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Not too bad. No. You know, there was some all right, some - you know, how they are like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Not too bad, I liked him very much, the son especially, very nice. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you feel about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well I got on very well I must say with them. They were very kind to me indeed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I liked it very much. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You didn't work after that, you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Married after that, that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You say that you did have to go to work after that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, during the war, I had to go to - working in the Bon Marche.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Shop assistant again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Shop assistant, yes. Well they - it was work in shifts see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 This was during the last war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Because - I could have taken so
meone - but - it was - wasn't well see, yes, you don't know who's who you see so - I had a friend in the Bon Marche, Miss Harris, she was the manageress there and she come over on Friday night and asked me - would I come. And glad - I was glad to go to te
ll you the truth then. It was only Scott Road. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well in the beginning I would have liked - I would have liked to have gone nursing. You know, that's what I would have liked to have don
e really. But - mother thought it was better to go - into the shop like my sister, see that's what - the snag really was 'cos of Min you see. But the nursing I would have liked - to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You served an apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes, to a trade union. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you take part in any of this activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, we didn't - only just paid our contribution you know to the - union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well they didn't really have the same interest did they you know. No, I shouldn't say they did really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you feel there was a division of interest among workers? Some people say that in those days ther
e was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Well not when I was working, because - more or less we were all the same then like, you understand what I mean, yes, we'd all done our - service you see, yes. Not then. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What about your life at ho-m after you left school, did you continue to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 With your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. In fact, we were - we were more together than ever weren't we. Min and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were you both in the same shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Same shop as me, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 In the both shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Yes. Yes. Although Min went - my sister went to Bargood for a while. Yes. After the other shop closed down. Artie Jones - W.L. Evans closed down my sister went to Bargoyd, and then she came back after and went back to Artie Jones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, no different, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You still went to chapel three times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 After I got married you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 After you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. YES? We had to go to chapel, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Yes, regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. My mother was a Sunday school teacher you see. Yes. Oh lovely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You continued going to Sunday school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. 'Til - 'til I got married you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What were your views, after you left school and started work, you were still young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Well it was the same views I had really. 'Cos there wasn't any Liberals then was there, you know, it w
as mostly Labour and - Conservative and all that, wasn't it, we're still a Liberal though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Why did you think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - always been I suppose isn't it you know, you stick to the same things don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Were you a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you ever work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, I didn't do it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election ti-e?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I was asked, but I - didn't do it though. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anyone to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, I don't - no, they never interfered. No, they never interfered with anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You didn't have a vote then, you were too young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. YES. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Women didn't have the vote 'til later did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 After you started work how did you spend your spare time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well, in chapel mostly you know like unless we were going to - concerts or anything like that like.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 It was the same as before was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 The same really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You didn't do anything different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No, nothing different. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes, sometimes we used to go out walking you know. Walking mostly. All round - round the mountains and
 things we used to see or walked to Aberant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Who would you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Friends mostly, my friends. I had a - a lifelong friend, Janet. Yes. Or my sister like. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you make any new friends at this time, after leaving school and starting work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I met my - yes, I made some friends with the - in the - in - the work you know, in the shop, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Boyfriends or girlfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Girlfriends, yes, 'cos - we used to stay - we - we used to go to Pontsticket a lot, stay the weekends in Ponst
icket, with a friend from the shop. And her father was - he was inspector of the works - of the Water Works up there. In Ponsticket. Used to go there and then - and then we used to walk from there then to Ponsarn to chapel, to the Pensarn church like you 
know. It was lovely. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you ever bring her home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Yes. She would come home - pretty regular with us. If she lose - lose the train in the night - go to Pensarn get - she'd come and stay with us then 'til the next - time you know, next train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Was she your special friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You did say you had another special friend?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes, my cousin, yes, yes, she's wonderful she is now today, yes, friendly today, very very kind. Her mother died now you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 That wasn't the one that was living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Where would you go with your friends then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well walking a lot you know and go to the pictures. IN a whole - once in a while like and - mostly walking though we used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Oh always. Yes. Oh we had an awful time - one time in - when I was in - I shouldn't go to dances see, shouldn't go to any dances. So this particular night they had a - a da
nce from the - with the shop in - in Kirkups Hall in Merthyr, and - I had to leave at twelve when the dancing was starting, see, my mother was so narrow you see. I was only attending the buffet for the time being, but I had to leave. She came down to meet
 
me all the way. Not religious to come to a hall like that. And she come down - specially, yes, I shouldn't go to any dances. Very very narrow. And my mother thought it was evil you know to go to dances, that's silly isn't it. YES. When I go to anywhere no
w to the - when I used to go late to these - functions at the work you know, couldn't dance. But if there was games it was all right like you know. My mother was very narrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 She never allowed you to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 How did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Oh we cried our eyes out very often. 'Cos me mum couldn't see any good in it you see and there was no - it wasn't bad you see at all. I mean there were bad and good there but you didn't want to mix with the bad people if they didn't wish to. Mum c
ouldn't see anything good in dancing at all. And years ago they never did you see did they. No. They never went themselves you see and then they - sort of - we sort of had to do what we were told you know. Oh many a night I've broke my heart over that. Ye
s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Your mother wouldn't relent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
No. No. No, no, you can do anything you like there, she says, but you can't do that. And the time see, 'cos they don't start 'til about one o'clock in the morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 And she came down to meet you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Ye
s, all the way down, it was about two miles from home wasn't it. So I shouldn't go. No. Shouldn't go. Nor Minnie. And all the other girls were enjoying themselves you know, they all used to say, oh there's mean your mother is Doris, she said. I said, well
 
I couldn't help it, I said, she don't like it and then - and I wouldn't go against her you know. No. Oh she thought dancing was terrible. Of course there was such a lot of old talk years ago wasn't there in dances, you know that like don't you. You know, 
it's not so open as it is today you see, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 So they expected to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. When - in the beginning. Oh had to be home by nine o'clock. Mum was frightened 'cos 
of the way you see we had that's what it was you see. We had such a - long way - back from Befarthfa church to our house, it was only mountains you see, all the way, like tips like. Years ago. Well you see old Crawshaw, you see, I'll tell you this, Crawsh
a
w years ago see was against Gefarthfa church. He never wanted a church built there so he built these tips all around it. He was that annoyed with them. Yes. Years ago. He was a blooming atheist he was you see. And - he was very very annoyed when they buil
t that church. So he built these tips all around it so it could be hidden. Funny isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 The church was in the middle of the tips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You think that's what made your mother careful of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I think more than anything that she w
as nervous of - of - you'd never know who'd be about in the night like you know. I think she was worried about old tramps and stuff like that you know, 'cos they are around there. Oh yes. Take our own lighting see, torches. And I'll tell you what you used
 
to do years ago, put the candle in the jar. YES. To get the lighting, yes. YES. And I remember going Gellitdeg - Gellideg chapel, it's all along the line, it's like from here I should say to - well the bottom of this road, no further than that like, down 
b
y the works, and we used to put a candle in a - in a jar, and half the time it used to blow out you know, we were scared stiff. Oh we were scared stiff. Yes, used to go to choir over there in Gellideg like, at the chapel there, it's a lovely little chapel
 too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 So you used to go out most evenings did you when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 We used to go out with my friends then, yes. Either to this little cwrddan or walking like you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 You'd still go to the activities in the chapel would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 Well - I'd go - I'd go to sewing class. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 What would you do in the evenings when you left school and started work in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 I remember having cwrddan mawr, used to cwrddan in the weekdays then and they used to have two - two min
isters, not one. WE used to listen to - listen to the two ministers. And that's the very night that we had this - this dance, but I had to go to cwrddan mawr first before I could go, yes indeed, that's the truth in't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12022365 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 And you had to come out before it finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10838799 DH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2901470\charrsid10176723 
Yes, I couldn't - I had to come out before it finished. Yes. They were very very na-row see you know, but I don't think they were narrow, I think they were more frightened you know in case something would happen like you know. Yes. Yes,
 we used to sit down if you remember for two minutes like. Today you can't sit for quarter of an hour.
\par }}